Quote: <i>Hadramphus tuberculatus</i> (the Canterbury knobbled weevil) has been largely forgotten - a category X (presumed extinct) species ... whether the knobbled weevil is one of the mysterious pollinators of <i>Aciphylla</i> has yet to be established.
